bug: the standard Memory module is not multi-locale-safe

I am observing the failure under these conditions:

* Default settings for comm=gasnet on my desktop (gnu/linux64).

* -nl3 and higher, intermittently.
  -nl1 and -nl2 are always succeeding.
  It fails with -nl3 more consistently than with -nl4.
  It has not failed under start_test.

* It is sufficient just to compile $CHPL_HOME/modules/standard/Memory.chpl
  and run it with --memTrack -nl3.

  The code I got in .chpl merely adds some frills, e.g. ensures
  memoryUsed() is invoked.

Since under start_test it is more likely to succeed (in my tries, anyways),
I am setting .skipif to true to avoid pervasive false positives.

The crash always happens on node 0.
